Business Brief -- British Airways PLC:
   Airline, New Consortium
   Buy Swissair-Run Carrier
Delta flies 19 domestic and international routes, serving
Hamburg, Stuttgart, Bremen, Brussels, Paris, Geneva, Zurich
and Basel, among others.
   Delta, which will be renamed Deutsche BA, will replace
BA's current Berlin-based German domestic service, which the
German government has ordered closed by the end of this year.
British Airways owns 49% of Deutsche BA. The rest is split
between Commerzbank AG, Berliner Bank AG and Bayerische
Vereinsbank AG.